CONDOLENCES: Expresses the condolences of the House of Representatives on the death
of William "Billy" Henry D'Aquilla
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To express the condolences of the House of Representatives upon the death of William
3 "Billy" Henry D'Aquilla.
4 WHEREAS, it is with immense sadness and profound regret that the House of
5 Representatives of the Legislature of Louisiana has learned of the passing, on April 12,
6 2026, of William "Billy" Henry D'Aquilla; and
7 WHEREAS, Billy was born on September 8, 1940, in Fort Adams, Mississippi, to
8 Frank and Velma Stutzmann D'Aquilla; and
9 WHEREAS, though Billy was born in Mississippi, he dedicated his life to the people
10 of St. Francisville, Louisiana; he was elected as town alderman and mayor pro tempore in
11 1972, and he was elected mayor in 1984; and
12 WHEREAS, Billy proudly and humbly presided over St. Francisville's town
13 government until his retirement in 2020; he served nearly five decades with unwavering
14 dedication and guided the town through seasons of growth, challenge, and celebration; and
15 WHEREAS, Billy was known for his open-door policy, humor, and tireless
16 advocacy, and he truly valued every voice in the community; he was also the sole proprietor
17 of a popular local grocery store for many years, and he went on to work as a sales associate
18 for National American Wholesale; and
19 WHEREAS, Billy's life was a testament to the power of service, compassion, and
20 hometown pride; and
